flowRoot.flowPara: Pass the bight down through the hole, up around the edge of the sole and under the trailing rope heading towards the heel.
Allow length for the heel strap then insert the bight into the hole from the top. Bring the bight around the shoe and pass it through the heel loop, heading towards the toe.
Pass the loose ends through the toe hole. Untwist the rope through the whole shoe and adjust to fit. Then secure the loose ends with a figure of eight knot.
Form a larks head with the end of the bight then pass the trailing end through the loop. Try to keep the cord from twisting out as you will need to massage them out later.
